o-control-when-the-textbox-text-updates-the-source.md).  \n  \n## See Also  \n [Binding Sources Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/binding-sources-overview.md)   \n [Data Binding Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/data-binding-overview.md)   \n [How-to Topics](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/data-binding-how-to-topics.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,75],"content":"How to: Implement Property Change Notification | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"How to: Implement Property Change Notification | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,63]}]},{"pos":[551,597],"content":"How to: Implement Property Change Notification","linkify":"How to: Implement Property Change Notification","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Implement Property Change Notification","pos":[0,46]}]},{"content":"To support <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Data.BindingMode&gt;</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Data.BindingMode&gt;</ph> binding to enable your binding target properties to automatically reflect the dynamic changes of the binding source (for example, to have the preview pane updated automatically when the user edits a form), your class needs to provide the proper property changed notifications.","pos":[598,966],"source":"To support <xref:System.Windows.Data.BindingMode> or <xref:System.Windows.Data.BindingMode> binding to enable your binding target properties to automatically reflect the dynamic changes of the binding source (for example, to have the preview pane updated automatically when the user edits a form), your class needs to provide the proper property changed notifications."},{"content":"This example shows how to create a class that implements <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.ComponentModel.INotifyPropertyChanged&gt;</ph>.","pos":[967,1076],"source":" This example shows how to create a class that implements <xref:System.ComponentModel.INotifyPropertyChanged>."},{"pos":[1085,1092],"content":"Example","linkify":"Example","nodes":[{"c